            "text": {
              "status": "generated",
              "div": "<div xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\"><h3>Annotation</h3><table class=\"hl7__eu__lab__report\"><tr><th>Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us</th></tr><tr><td>Laboratory results show borderline elevated HbA1c (5.9%), indicating prediabetes. Glucose is mildly low (66.1 mg/dL), which may be due to fasting or other factors. Chloride is slightly elevated (109 mmol/L), but other electrolytes, renal function, and calcium are within normal limits. No acute abnormalities; recommend clinical correlation and monitoring of glucose metabolism.</td></tr></table></div>"
